  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nWhen calling `NewDocumentDecoder` the token size for the buffer is the default which is NOT changable. Larger documents (which is likely when using a yaml separator) causes a `bufio.Scanner: token too long`\r\n\r\nThis was uncovered using kudo... the issue is https://github.com/kudobuilder/kudo/issues/1397\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n1. size limitation should be documented if they exist\r\n2. token size should be calling code managed\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nCall `NewDocumentDecoder` with a doc larger than token size\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nThe fixing PR https://github.com/kudobuilder/kudo/pull/1400 provides more detail if needed.\r\n\r\nCode concern is: https://github.com/kubernetes/apimachinery/blob/release-1.6/pkg/util/yaml/decoder.go#L94\r\n\r\nduplicate of https://github.com/kubernetes/apimachinery/issues/89 which I will now close\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):  1.17\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: \r\n- OS (e.g: `cat /etc/os-release`):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Network plugin and version (if this is a network-related bug):\r\n- Others:\r\n",
